{[showcards N:D5]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown.

Partner led the \SJ, won by dummy's \SQ. The \D5 is now played from dummy. What do you play?

Play the \D2. Considering that South opened 1NT, he must have the \DQ for this play to make sense. 

So if you put on your \DA, South will have TWO \D winners established. If instead you play low, then South cannot get a second \D trick and will have to look elsewhere for his ninth trick. As you can see, he is not going to be able to find it.}
[Play "W"]SJ

