{[showcards S:H2]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

Your lead of the \CJ was won by South with the \CA. South then played the \H2 and you must decide whether to split your honors.

Play the \H4, do not split your Honors.

South's bidding showed at least 5 \Hs, so assuming he holds both the \H A Q, it would be silly for him to finesse the \H9 on the first trump play.

As it turns out, when you play low South calls for dummy's \HK, East's \HQ falls and you now have 2 trump tricks. If you had played the \H10 you would have tossed away the setting trick.}
[Play "W"]CJ

